!! Engine identifier

This adapter registers as `MindElixir`. Use this name in:

* `$:/config/rimir/mindmap/default-engine`
* `mm.engine` on view tiddlers
* `engine="MindElixir"` on a `<$mindmap>` widget

!! Engine options (passed via `mm.options`)

|!Key |!Type |!Default |!Effect |
|`direction` |0/1/2 |2 |0=LEFT, 1=RIGHT, 2=SIDE (both sides) |
|`draggable` |boolean |true |Allow node drag-reparenting |
|`contextMenu` |boolean |true |Show mind-elixir's right-click menu |
|`toolBar` |boolean |true |Show mind-elixir's built-in toolbar |
|`keypress` |boolean |true |Bind keyboard shortcuts (Tab=child, Enter=sibling, Delete=remove, F2=rename) |

Additional mind-elixir options pass through verbatim. See [[mind-elixir docs|https://docs.mind-elixir.com]].

Example view tiddler:

```
mm.producer:  knowledge-tree
mm.args:      {"area":"llm"}
mm.engine:    MindElixir
mm.options:   {"direction":2, "draggable":true, "keypress":false}
mm.overlay:   $:/state/rimir/mindmap/views/llm/overlay
```

!! Op translation table

|!mind-elixir operation |!Emitted Op |!Notes |
|`finishEdit` |`{ op: "rename", id, label }` |Emitted when the user finishes inline editing |
|`removeNode` |`{ op: "removeNode", id }` |Explicit user delete |
|`addChild` |`{ op: "addNode", parent, node }` |New node created in canvas |
|`moveNode` |`{ op: "reparent", id, newParent }` |Drag-reparent |
|`moveNodeBefore` |`{ op: "reparent", id, newParent }` |Drag-reorder before sibling |
|`moveNodeAfter` |`{ op: "reparent", id, newParent }` |Drag-reorder after sibling |
|`beginEdit`, `selectNode`, `expandNode` |(none) |Informational, no overlay write |
|other |`{ op: "setAttr", id, key: "mx:lastOp", value: name }` |Round-trip preservation only |

!! Flag-attribute support

The `rimir/mindmap` 0.2.13+ flag decorator stamps engine-specific `mx:*` attrs and the engine-neutral `mx:flags` / `mx:flag-classes` channels. The adapter translates them in two places:

!!! In `toMENode()` → inline `style.*`

|!MDOM attr |!mind-elixir style property |!Notes |
|`mx:text-color` |`style.color` |Overrides the `core:color` auto-contrast colour |
|`mx:font-weight` |`style.fontWeight` |Strings like `bold`, `600` |
|`mx:font-style` |`style.fontStyle` |Typically `italic` |
|`mx:text-transform` |`style.textTransform` |`uppercase` / `lowercase` / `capitalize` |
|`mx:opacity` |`style.opacity` |`"0.5"` etc. |
|`mx:border` |`style.outline` + `outlineOffset: 2px` |//Outline, not border// — the topic bubble's `border` is used for the focus ring |
|`mx:font-size-scale` |`style.fontSize` as `<n>em` |E.g. `mx:font-size-scale: "1.2"` → `style.fontSize = "1.2em"` |
|`mx:icons` |Prepended to `meNode.icons` |Pipe-separated glyphs (decorator-ordered DESCENDING priority); `core:icon` joins on the right |

Empty / unset attrs do not pollute `meNode.style` — every branch guards on truthy value.

!!! In `_applyTooltips()` → DOM `data-*` attrs

|!MDOM attr |!DOM attribute |!Use |
|`mx:flags` |`data-mm-flags` |Space-separated flag names. Match individual flags via `me-tpc[data-mm-flags~="name"]` |
|`mx:flag-classes` |`data-mm-flag-classes` |Custom class tokens from `mm.flag-class` |
|`core:synthetic` (=== `true`) |`data-mm-synthetic="yes"` |Distinguishes synthetic group nodes (chain/axis) from tiddler-backed leaves |

The native `title=` attribute on each `<me-tpc>` is also driven from MDOM attrs: `_applyTooltips` joins the producer's `core:tooltip` and the flag-decorator's `mx:flag-tooltip` with a newline (core first, flag block below). If both are absent the attribute is removed, so empty hovers don't render an empty native bubble.

Each is stamped only when the source attr is non-empty; the adapter clears stale attrs when a previously-flagged node no longer matches. CSS authors get the full token-list semantic without needing to know the engine's internal class structure.

!! Public method surface

|!Method |!Effect |
|`init(element, mdom, options)` |Construct, mount, bind events |
|`update(mdom)` |Replace data via mind-elixir's `refresh()` |
|`focus(id)` |Select the node in mind-elixir |
|`expand(id)` / `collapse(id)` |Toggle a branch |
|`destroy()` |Remove listeners and DOM |
|`on("op", fn)` |Subscribe to translated overlay ops |
|`on("select", fn)` |Subscribe to selection events (fn receives node id) |

